	more abundant when C/O < 1, whereas CH4, HCN, and C2H2 gain significantly
	in abundance when C/O > 1. Other notable species like N-2 and NH3
	that do not contain carbon or oxygen are relatively unaffected by
	the C/O ratio. Disequilibrium processes tend to enhance the abundance
