   (specific chlorides and sulfides, not silicates), may in part be
   responsible for the steep spectrum of G1 229B observed in the near-IR
   below 1 mu m We assemble a temperature sequence of chemical transitions
   in substellar atmospheres that may be used to anchor and define a
   sequence of spectral types for substellar objects with T-eff's from
   similar to 2200 to similar to 100 K.},
