   public databases, laboratory data that is not yet in the public
   databases, and our own numerical calculations. We combine these
   opacities with abundances computed from a chemical equilibrium model
   using recently revised solar abundances to compute mean opacities. The
   chemical equilibrium calculation accounts for the settling of
   condensates in a gravitational field and is applicable to ultracool
   dwarf and extrasolar planetary atmospheres, but not circumstellar disks.
   We find that the inclusion of alkali atomic opacity substantially
   increases the mean opacities over those currently in the literature at
   densities relevant to the atmospheres and interiors of giant planets and
